<subSubSection lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1805,2010]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1877,1902]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Description.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[365,452,1877,1902]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1025,1047]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1003]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1003]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 16. Haliclona (Gellius) sp. aff. flagellifera (Ridley &amp; Dendy, 1886), a, habitus of RMNH Por. 9783 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of surface skeleton of ditto, c – e, SEM images of spicules of RMH Por. 9921, c, oxea, d, flagellated sigma, e, sigma." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272967/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
a) Encrusting with lobes and upright lamellar projections. The three samples were obtained from the same station, but were disintegrated in small cm-sized fragments making it difficult to describe the overall shape in more detail. The surface is irregular, punctate, with small oscules elevated on low cushions. The color (in alcohol) is pinkish light brown. The consistency is soft and fragile.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272967/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" targetBox="[151,1436,193,1003]" targetPageId="27">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1435,1025,1108]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,282,1025,1047]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">FIGURE 16</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[297,496,1025,1047]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicName box="[297,398,1025,1047]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">Haliclona</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Gray, 1867" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[414,489,1025,1047]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Gellius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">Gellius</taxonomicName>
)
</emphasis>
sp. 
<taxonomicName authority="Ridley &amp; Dendy, 1886" authorityName="Ridley &amp; Dendy" authorityYear="1886" box="[540,955,1025,1047]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="flagellifera">
aff. 
<emphasis box="[582,695,1025,1047]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">flagellifera</emphasis>
(Ridley &amp; Dendy, 1886)
</taxonomicName>
, a, habitus of RMNH Por. 9783 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of surface skeleton of ditto, c–e, SEM images of spicules of RMH Por. 9921, c, oxea, d, flagellated sigma, e, sigma.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1147,1928]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1147,1172]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Skeleton.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[325,406,1147,1172]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1025,1047]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1003]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1003]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 16. Haliclona (Gellius) sp. aff. flagellifera (Ridley &amp; Dendy, 1886), a, habitus of RMNH Por. 9783 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of surface skeleton of ditto, c – e, SEM images of spicules of RMH Por. 9921, c, oxea, d, flagellated sigma, e, sigma." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272967/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
b) The choanosome shows a loose reticulation of ascending tracts which have 2–3 spicules and interconnecting single spicules, but overall the skeleton is rather confused without binding spongin. The surface skeleton is unispicular, but it is discontinuous where there are large subdermal spaces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1147,1928]" box="[199,946,1255,1280]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,1255,1280]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Spicules.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[319,399,1255,1280]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1025,1047]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1003]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1003]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 16. Haliclona (Gellius) sp. aff. flagellifera (Ridley &amp; Dendy, 1886), a, habitus of RMNH Por. 9783 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of surface skeleton of ditto, c – e, SEM images of spicules of RMH Por. 9921, c, oxea, d, flagellated sigma, e, sigma." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272967/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
c–e) Oxeas, flagellated sigmas, ‘normal’ sigmas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1147,1928]" box="[151,1128,1291,1316]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Oxeas (
<figureCitation box="[236,318,1291,1316]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1025,1047]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1003]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1003]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 16. Haliclona (Gellius) sp. aff. flagellifera (Ridley &amp; Dendy, 1886), a, habitus of RMNH Por. 9783 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of surface skeleton of ditto, c – e, SEM images of spicules of RMH Por. 9921, c, oxea, d, flagellated sigma, e, sigma." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272967/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
c), slightly curved, elongated-fusiform, 226– 
<emphasis box="[818,860,1292,1316]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">319</emphasis>
–358 
<date box="[923,969,1292,1316]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="2011-10">x 11</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[985,1034,1292,1316]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">12.7</emphasis>
–14 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1147,1928]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Flagellated sigmas (
<figureCitation box="[377,459,1327,1352]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1025,1047]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1003]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1003]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 16. Haliclona (Gellius) sp. aff. flagellifera (Ridley &amp; Dendy, 1886), a, habitus of RMNH Por. 9783 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of surface skeleton of ditto, c – e, SEM images of spicules of RMH Por. 9921, c, oxea, d, flagellated sigma, e, sigma." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272967/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
d), strongly assymetrical, with the shorter apex angularly incurved and the longer apex at first curving in and at the end curving out again, longer axis 72– 
<emphasis box="[897,939,1364,1388]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">109</emphasis>
–159, shorter axis 51– 
<emphasis box="[1188,1216,1363,1388]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">63</emphasis>
–75 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1147,1928]" box="[151,1136,1399,1424]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Normal sigmas (
<figureCitation box="[336,418,1399,1424]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1025,1047]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1003]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1003]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 16. Haliclona (Gellius) sp. aff. flagellifera (Ridley &amp; Dendy, 1886), a, habitus of RMNH Por. 9783 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of surface skeleton of ditto, c – e, SEM images of spicules of RMH Por. 9921, c, oxea, d, flagellated sigma, e, sigma." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272967/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
e), symmetrical, with slightly incurving apices, 42– 
<emphasis box="[993,1042,1400,1424]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">51.5</emphasis>
–56 µm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1147,1928]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,504,1435,1460]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Distribution and ecology.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[514,601,1436,1460]" name="Guyana" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Guyana</collectingCountry>
Shelf, 
<collectingRegion box="[686,770,1435,1460]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Florida</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[784,858,1435,1460]" name="Belize" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<collectingRegion box="[784,858,1435,1460]" country="Belize" name="Belize" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Belize</collectingRegion>
</collectingCountry>
, elsewhere reported from all over the world (
<typeStatus box="[1386,1436,1436,1460]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">type</typeStatus>
locality is Marion 
<collectingCountry box="[356,424,1471,1496]" name="Iceland" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Island</collectingCountry>
in the 
<collectingRegion box="[500,601,1471,1496]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Southern" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Southern</collectingRegion>
Indian Ocean), depth in the region: 
<quantity box="[1003,1118,1472,1496]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" metricValueMax="4.1" metricValueMin="0.2" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="m" value="215.0" valueMax="410.0" valueMin="20.0">20–410 m</quantity>
, elsewhere down to 
<quantity box="[1345,1432,1472,1496]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.378" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="m" value="1378.0">1378 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1147,1928]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1507,1532]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Remarks.</emphasis>
This very characteristic species comprises most likely a species complex, because the published records encompass an almost cosmopolitan distribution: e.g. the 
<collectingRegion box="[909,1010,1543,1568]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Southern" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Southern</collectingRegion>
Ocean (
<bibRefCitation author="Ridley" box="[1112,1378,1543,1568]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refString="Ridley, S. O. &amp; Dendy, A. (1886) Preliminary report on the Monaxonida collected by H. M. S. ' Challenger'. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, (5) 18, 325 - 351, 470 - 493." type="journal article" year="1886">Ridley &amp; Dendy 1886</bibRefCitation>
), the Arctic Ocean (
